<headline>Beach Hazards Statement issued June 26 at 3:36PM EDT until June 27 at 5:00AM EDT by NWS NorthernIndiana</headline>
<description>...BEACH HAZARDS STATEMENT REMAINS IN EFFECT THROUGH LATE
TONIGHT...
* WHAT...High wave action and dangerous currents will create
dangerous swimming conditions. Waves of 1 to 3 feet will build
to 3 to 5 feet into tonight.
* WHERE...Berrien county.
* WHEN...From 10 AM EDT this morning through late tonight.
* IMPACTS...Strong currents can pull swimmers into deeper water
and high waves can sweep people off piers.</description>
<instruction>Remain out of the water to avoid hazardous swimming conditions.
Do not venture out on piers.</instruction>
